> **Colour rule:** Never hardcode hex colour values in SwiftUI views. Always
> use `Color("TokenName")` from the asset catalog or a typed `Color`
> extension. Brand tokens are defined in `core/design/colors.json`.
> See `.cursor/rules/ui/design-system.mdc`.

# SwiftUI Patterns

- Use `FeatureView` / `FeatureViewContents` per `.cursor/rules/ui/agent-ios.mdc`.
- Put `#Preview` on `FeatureViewContents` only, not on `FeatureView`.
- Use `ViewState<T>` for screen state: Loading, Success(T), Error, Refreshing(T).
- See root rules for full view structure.
